name: Two Six Code
title: TSC
definition: Identifies a code assigned to a trunk group or CCS Link Set.
usageNotes: Required when the ACT field on the ASR Form is “N”, the first position of the REQTYP field on the ASR Form is “M” and the RT field is “F”.
Prohibited when the RT field is “B”.
fieldNotes: The code is unique to each established trunk group or CCS Link Set.
